1
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:32,680
What about Boss Noo?

2
00:02:33,480 --> 00:02:34,560
He's still alive, right?

3
00:02:34,640 --> 00:02:38,080
Yes. His men got him out in time.

4
00:02:38,600 --> 00:02:41,000
The police shot him,
leaving him dragging his leg.

5
00:02:41,760 --> 00:02:43,360
Whose car is this, Dad?

6
00:02:43,440 --> 00:02:46,440
It's your car, my daughter.

7
00:02:46,520 --> 00:02:48,480
Mine? Really mine?

8
00:02:50,160 --> 00:02:52,000
When you become a singer someday,

9
00:02:52,080 --> 00:02:55,240
I'll be your first fan,
buying a plushie for you.

10
00:02:55,320 --> 00:02:57,240
PREVIOUS EPISODE

11
00:02:57,960 --> 00:03:00,440
But I remember, it really was here before.

12
00:03:00,520 --> 00:03:02,160
Maybe it's in the props room.

13
00:03:02,240 --> 00:03:04,320
-Let's go check.
-Okay, let's go.

14
00:03:13,160 --> 00:03:16,240
Don't tell me that bear
ended up with Sonrak?

15
00:03:17,200 --> 00:03:18,800
Just go be his girlfriend.

16
00:03:18,880 --> 00:03:20,960
-A girlfriend?
-Yeah.

17
00:03:31,640 --> 00:03:32,680
Aew!

18
00:03:33,440 --> 00:03:34,600
That was close!

19
00:03:35,120 --> 00:03:37,440
What's wrong with you?
Are you having hallucinations?

20
00:03:37,520 --> 00:03:40,080
I thought those guys
sent someone to take me out.

21
00:03:41,840 --> 00:03:44,760
See? Taking jobs without checking first.

22
00:03:45,280 --> 00:03:48,560
Boss Noo wants to silence you.
Boss Singha's after you.

23
00:03:49,160 --> 00:03:51,600
Aw, you worthless mutt!

24
00:03:52,840 --> 00:03:56,280
Those bastards, I won't
let them mess with me.

25
00:03:57,360 --> 00:03:59,800
I'm the one dealing with them first.

26
00:04:01,480 --> 00:04:04,160
Yeah, if you think you can.
Just a heads-up.

27
00:04:04,240 --> 00:04:06,160
Don't get into trouble.

28
00:04:06,240 --> 00:04:08,440
Just being here with me is risky enough.

29
00:04:08,520 --> 00:04:10,560
If the boss finds out, I'm in big trouble.

30
00:04:13,320 --> 00:04:14,280
Aw.

31
00:04:15,120 --> 00:04:17,160
I promise, no one will know.

32
00:04:19,880 --> 00:04:22,440
I have to hurry.
They're shipping the drugs.

33
00:04:23,560 --> 00:04:24,520
Where?

34
00:04:26,920 --> 00:04:27,840
Why do you want to know?

35
00:04:37,040 --> 00:04:37,960
Hey!

36
00:04:38,480 --> 00:04:39,440
Be careful!

37
00:04:39,520 --> 00:04:40,520
Got it.

38
00:04:45,320 --> 00:04:46,400
How's it going, Tia?

39
00:04:46,480 --> 00:04:47,960
All good. No problems.

40
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:51,880
Good. Be careful.
Which box is the client's?

41
00:04:52,760 --> 00:04:53,600
That one.

42
00:04:54,360 --> 00:04:55,480
Be careful with that one.

43
00:04:57,160 --> 00:04:58,240
I'm here.

44
00:04:59,120 --> 00:05:01,840
Keep an eye on the shop.
I'll deliver the goods myself.

45
00:05:15,520 --> 00:05:17,360
What's in these crates?

46
00:05:17,880 --> 00:05:20,200
Curious, huh? Hey,
open it up and show him.

47
00:05:23,520 --> 00:05:24,720
Whoa, bro!

48
00:05:25,920 --> 00:05:27,880
Why'd you bring so many of these?

49
00:05:29,520 --> 00:05:31,960
-Here, take one!
-Hey, whoa!

50
00:05:32,720 --> 00:05:35,680
It's a grenade, Chart!
If I miss it, we're all gonna die!

51
00:05:37,040 --> 00:05:40,040
Relax! The pin's still in.

52
00:05:40,120 --> 00:05:43,240
I've never seen a grenade up close
like this before.

53
00:05:44,360 --> 00:05:45,200
Give it to me.

54
00:05:46,080 --> 00:05:47,440
You scaredy-cat.

55
00:05:50,560 --> 00:05:51,960
But anyway…

56
00:05:53,200 --> 00:05:54,880
Today you're coming to work with me.

57
00:05:56,280 --> 00:05:57,360
But today,

58
00:05:57,440 --> 00:06:00,720
I was supposed to take Mr. Sonrak
to the charity event with Kamnan Pong.

59
00:06:01,640 --> 00:06:04,000
Mr. Sonrak's going by van today.

60
00:06:04,800 --> 00:06:08,120
The boss ordered me
to take you to work with me.

61
00:06:10,960 --> 00:06:11,960
Where are we going?

62
00:06:12,640 --> 00:06:13,760
You don't need to know.

63
00:06:14,520 --> 00:06:15,600
Just take it.

64
00:06:17,880 --> 00:06:19,440
And follow me.

65
00:06:20,840 --> 00:06:22,360
Can he handle this?

66
00:06:34,840 --> 00:06:36,720
Come on. Hurry up!

67
00:06:49,360 --> 00:06:50,280
Hey, Wong!

68
00:06:51,160 --> 00:06:52,920
Today's the big shipment.

69
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:55,880
Don't mess it up,
or the boss will kill us.

70
00:06:58,680 --> 00:06:59,680
Hey!

71
00:07:00,280 --> 00:07:01,160
What are you doing?

72
00:07:03,080 --> 00:07:05,960
I'm gonna call HR to tell them
I'm going with you today.

73
00:07:06,040 --> 00:07:07,000
No way.

74
00:07:07,080 --> 00:07:08,480
Today,

75
00:07:08,560 --> 00:07:11,800
phones are off until the job's done.

76
00:07:15,080 --> 00:07:16,880
Come on. Move.

77
00:07:19,280 --> 00:07:20,560
Let's go.

78
00:07:20,640 --> 00:07:21,680
Hey, Chaiya!

79
00:07:22,200 --> 00:07:23,200
Where are you going?

80
00:07:24,840 --> 00:07:27,120
I'm going with Chart for an urgent job.

81
00:07:27,200 --> 00:07:28,560
-What about Mr. Sonrak?
-Hey.

82
00:07:29,960 --> 00:07:32,680
Today you're going with Chang.

83
00:07:32,760 --> 00:07:34,320
Chaiya's busy.

84
00:07:34,400 --> 00:07:35,440
He's coming with me.

85
00:07:35,520 --> 00:07:36,840
-But Mr. Sonrak--
-Shut up.

86
00:07:37,720 --> 00:07:39,400
Enough talking. I'm in a rush.

87
00:07:39,920 --> 00:07:41,520
Get in the van now.

88
00:07:42,640 --> 00:07:43,760
Hey, hurry up.

89
00:07:56,800 --> 00:07:57,880
Mueangphrai.

90
00:07:58,960 --> 00:08:02,040
I'm sorry. The doctor didn't finish
until yesterday afternoon.

91
00:08:02,120 --> 00:08:03,960
I saw it was getting dark,

92
00:08:04,040 --> 00:08:05,960
so I stayed in Bangkok for another night.

93
00:08:06,040 --> 00:08:08,160
Good thing you stayed there.

94
00:08:08,240 --> 00:08:11,440
It's safer than traveling late.
Have you eaten yet?

95
00:08:12,040 --> 00:08:15,600
I'd rather eat at home.
I don't want to draw attention.

96
00:08:16,120 --> 00:08:17,560
Where's the car parked?

97
00:08:18,080 --> 00:08:19,000
Over there.

98
00:08:19,520 --> 00:08:20,520
-Let's go.
-Let's go.

99
00:08:29,520 --> 00:08:31,000
We need to talk.

100
00:08:38,120 --> 00:08:39,159
Come with me.

101
00:08:40,360 --> 00:08:41,559
I won't hurt you.

102
00:08:56,520 --> 00:08:58,840
Can you lift the cloth off your face?

103
00:09:01,360 --> 00:09:03,080
No, Kamnan! What are you doing?

104
00:09:03,160 --> 00:09:04,440
This isn't right.

105
00:09:04,520 --> 00:09:06,720
I know it's not right.

106
00:09:08,840 --> 00:09:09,840
But it's necessary.

107
00:09:12,520 --> 00:09:15,040
So nothing's left hanging between us.

108
00:09:18,720 --> 00:09:20,840
Ever since I saw you last,

109
00:09:22,760 --> 00:09:23,600
I haven't been able to sleep.

110
00:09:23,680 --> 00:09:25,320
Where did you see us?

111
00:09:25,400 --> 00:09:26,600
In front of the house.

112
00:09:38,880 --> 00:09:41,120
I really want to know who you really are.

113
00:09:49,520 --> 00:09:50,560
Wilai!

114
00:10:06,680 --> 00:10:08,160
You remember me, don't you?

115
00:10:21,680 --> 00:10:22,560
Onanong.

116
00:10:24,920 --> 00:10:25,800
Yes.

117
00:10:27,640 --> 00:10:29,320
I used to be Onanong.

118
00:10:31,240 --> 00:10:32,800
But now I'm Wilai.

119
00:10:34,840 --> 00:10:36,480
Wilai, which means beautiful,

120
00:10:38,240 --> 00:10:41,080
to match the ugliness I am now.

121
00:10:41,160 --> 00:10:42,280
Who…

122
00:10:44,400 --> 00:10:46,080
Who said you were dead?

123
00:10:46,600 --> 00:10:50,120
You know I can hardly believe my eyes!

124
00:10:51,600 --> 00:10:52,920
Disappointed, aren't you?

125
00:10:54,160 --> 00:10:56,920
Here I am. Go ahead!

126
00:10:57,440 --> 00:10:59,680
Kill me, torture me, do whatever you want!

127
00:10:59,760 --> 00:11:02,480
Why would I kill you, On?
Do you know how angry I was last time?

128
00:11:02,560 --> 00:11:04,800
I was really hurt by you, you know.

129
00:11:05,920 --> 00:11:09,440
Ever since you left, not a day goes by
that I don't think of you.

130
00:11:11,600 --> 00:11:12,880
I know…

131
00:11:14,200 --> 00:11:17,360
I was never in your thoughts.

132
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:22,680
Because your heart…

133
00:11:24,120 --> 00:11:26,240
belonged only to Phupha.

134
00:11:28,840 --> 00:11:29,680
Yes.

135
00:11:30,520 --> 00:11:33,520
In my heart, there's only Phupha.

136
00:11:35,120 --> 00:11:37,200
But we never did anything to each other.

137
00:11:37,280 --> 00:11:39,800
And the pictures Singha showed me.

138
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:42,280
What were they?

139
00:11:47,600 --> 00:11:49,720
You said there's an urgent matter.

140
00:11:49,800 --> 00:11:50,800
What's this about?

141
00:11:52,240 --> 00:11:53,920
On! Perfect timing. Come here.

142
00:11:58,520 --> 00:11:59,920
What are we talking about?

143
00:12:00,600 --> 00:12:03,040
It's about the music video, "Soft Heart".

144
00:12:03,760 --> 00:12:07,320
The director suggested you
as the lead actress

145
00:12:07,400 --> 00:12:09,000
and Phupha as the lead actor.

146
00:12:10,400 --> 00:12:11,680
What do you think, On?

147
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:15,000
Well, I'm fine with anything.

148
00:12:16,680 --> 00:12:17,920
And Phupha?

149
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:20,200
I think Singha might be more suitable.

150
00:12:22,120 --> 00:12:24,400
No, I'm not really available right now.

151
00:12:24,480 --> 00:12:27,520
I think Phupha is perfect for it.

152
00:12:29,200 --> 00:12:32,920
The reason I want you as the lead actor
is to promote you.

153
00:12:33,000 --> 00:12:34,960
So everyone gets to know you more.

154
00:12:35,040 --> 00:12:36,640
Look at other music labels.

155
00:12:36,720 --> 00:12:39,000
They promote their new artists
just like this.

156
00:12:42,480 --> 00:12:46,080
Then I'll leave it up to you, Kamnan.

157
00:12:47,240 --> 00:12:48,600
Alright, let's go with that.

158
00:12:53,080 --> 00:12:53,920
Yes.

159
00:13:04,600 --> 00:13:09,440
<i>Back then, my heart was strong</i>

160
00:13:10,720 --> 00:13:16,160
<i>As tough as a bar of steel</i>

161
00:13:16,920 --> 00:13:21,240
<i>So many men chased after me</i>

162
00:13:21,320 --> 00:13:24,280
<i>But I never paid them any mind</i>

163
00:13:24,360 --> 00:13:28,520
<i>Never gave them a thought</i>

164
00:13:29,440 --> 00:13:33,760
<i>But now, my heart is starting to weaken</i>

165
00:13:35,680 --> 00:13:41,280
<i>From the very first time I saw him</i>
<i>My heart started to waver</i>

166
00:13:41,800 --> 00:13:46,160
<i>What is it about this man?</i>

167
00:13:46,240 --> 00:13:49,320
<i>Every time I see his face</i>

168
00:13:49,400 --> 00:13:53,760
<i>My heart pounds</i>

169
00:13:54,800 --> 00:13:59,840
<i>Oh, my heart</i>

170
00:13:59,920 --> 00:14:05,440
<i>Why can't you stay composed?</i>

171
00:14:06,480 --> 00:14:11,040
<i>Just one teasing smile from him</i>

172
00:14:11,120 --> 00:14:13,480
<i>Before I knew it</i>

173
00:14:13,560 --> 00:14:18,040
<i>I'd already fallen for him</i>

174
00:14:19,440 --> 00:14:23,840
<i>Back then, my heart had never wavered</i>

175
00:14:25,480 --> 00:14:31,160
<i>Why does it burn, unable to escape?</i>

176
00:14:31,760 --> 00:14:35,560
<i>Like iron softened by fire</i>

177
00:14:35,640 --> 00:14:39,160
<i>Before the hammer strikes</i>

178
00:14:39,240 --> 00:14:44,120
<i>It bends on its own</i>

179
00:15:03,160 --> 00:15:08,360
<i>Oh, my heart</i>

180
00:15:08,440 --> 00:15:14,560
<i>Why can't you stay composed?</i>

181
00:15:15,080 --> 00:15:19,600
<i>Just one teasing smile from him</i>

182
00:15:19,680 --> 00:15:22,000
<i>Before I knew it</i>

183
00:15:22,080 --> 00:15:26,800
<i>I'd already fallen for him</i>

184
00:15:28,200 --> 00:15:32,800
<i>Back then, my heart had never wavered</i>

185
00:15:34,040 --> 00:15:39,800
<i>Why does it burn, unable to escape?</i>

186
00:15:40,320 --> 00:15:44,120
<i>Like iron softened by fire</i>

187
00:15:44,200 --> 00:15:47,720
<i>Before the hammer strikes</i>

188
00:15:47,800 --> 00:15:52,400
<i>It bends on its own</i>

189
00:15:59,680 --> 00:16:01,520
Next shot, we're moving into the story.

190
00:16:01,600 --> 00:16:03,080
Start with the romantic scene.

191
00:16:04,000 --> 00:16:06,600
Phupha, stand over there.
I want the two of you

192
00:16:06,680 --> 00:16:08,600
to stand and talk as if you're in love.

193
00:16:08,680 --> 00:16:10,480
Make it seem

194
00:16:10,560 --> 00:16:12,720
like you're alone together.

195
00:16:12,800 --> 00:16:15,080
The camera will be filming
from a distance.

196
00:16:16,880 --> 00:16:17,720
<i>Why can't you…</i>

197
00:16:17,800 --> 00:16:18,720
Got it?

198
00:16:18,800 --> 00:16:23,600
<i>Stay composed?</i>

199
00:16:23,680 --> 00:16:28,240
<i>Just one teasing smile from him</i>

200
00:16:28,320 --> 00:16:30,960
<i>Before I knew it</i>

201
00:16:31,040 --> 00:16:35,600
<i>I'd already fallen for him</i>

202
00:16:42,520 --> 00:16:45,200
How is it, Mr. Singha?
Are you happy with it?

203
00:16:47,160 --> 00:16:48,320
Good.

204
00:16:48,400 --> 00:16:50,520
It looks realistic.

205
00:16:51,920 --> 00:16:56,200
If I didn't know
this was the scene in a music video,

206
00:16:56,280 --> 00:16:58,240
I'd think they were having an affair.

207
00:17:03,920 --> 00:17:08,000
This scene shouldn't be
in the music video.

208
00:17:08,079 --> 00:17:09,800
Make sure to put a DVD copy aside for me.

209
00:17:11,240 --> 00:17:12,680
-Here, thanks a lot.
-Sure.

210
00:17:17,920 --> 00:17:20,880
I never thought the two of them
would dare do something like this.

211
00:17:23,880 --> 00:17:25,520
This isn't the first time.

212
00:17:27,200 --> 00:17:29,080
The crew has seen them
together many times.

213
00:17:29,160 --> 00:17:31,000
Thank you for telling me.

214
00:17:32,600 --> 00:17:34,040
You care for him so much.

215
00:17:34,640 --> 00:17:35,920
I never imagined

216
00:17:36,000 --> 00:17:39,080
that the person I loved most
would dare betray me.

217
00:17:39,960 --> 00:17:41,520
I never imagined it either

218
00:17:42,400 --> 00:17:44,560
that the owner of a music label like you

219
00:17:45,080 --> 00:17:48,240
would have such a filthy and cruel side.

220
00:17:48,920 --> 00:17:51,400
Cruel enough to even kill
the singer you made into a star.

221
00:17:51,480 --> 00:17:52,960
I can kill anyone.

222
00:17:54,000 --> 00:17:56,120
I can even kill you, Onanong!

223
00:17:58,360 --> 00:17:59,680
Come back! Get back here!

224
00:17:59,760 --> 00:18:00,880
Wait, Kamnan!

225
00:18:01,520 --> 00:18:05,400
That was the last time we ever met.

226
00:18:07,880 --> 00:18:12,120
After that, someone tried to kill Phupha,

227
00:18:12,640 --> 00:18:13,480
Namthip…

228
00:18:15,440 --> 00:18:16,680
and me.

229
00:18:20,680 --> 00:18:24,760
But the news said the three of you
had a love triangle,

230
00:18:24,840 --> 00:18:26,240
couldn't agree,

231
00:18:26,960 --> 00:18:29,000
and then the car went off the mountain.

232
00:18:29,080 --> 00:18:30,200
It's not true!

233
00:18:31,120 --> 00:18:32,880
They framed me.

234
00:18:34,320 --> 00:18:38,000
They showed you
the romantic scene of me with Phupha.

235
00:18:38,520 --> 00:18:40,080
It was staged.

236
00:18:40,720 --> 00:18:42,440
Because Phupha and I

237
00:18:43,080 --> 00:18:44,960
discovered their secret.

238
00:18:47,600 --> 00:18:48,800
What secret?

239
00:18:50,840 --> 00:18:52,880
On, tell me.

240
00:18:54,240 --> 00:18:56,160
What secret did you find out?

241
00:19:01,000 --> 00:19:02,040
Maybe…

242
00:19:04,240 --> 00:19:06,760
Kamnan, you were in on it with them.

243
00:19:12,680 --> 00:19:15,680
On, someone like me

244
00:19:16,880 --> 00:19:19,040
would never break the law.

245
00:19:19,120 --> 00:19:20,280
Never even thought of it.

246
00:19:23,480 --> 00:19:24,520
Just tell him.

247
00:19:25,040 --> 00:19:28,040
If he wants to kill us,
we wouldn't survive anyway.

248
00:19:28,560 --> 00:19:30,920
Say everything. Hold nothing back.

249
00:19:37,400 --> 00:19:38,400
On.

250
00:19:40,040 --> 00:19:41,320
Trust me.

251
00:19:42,840 --> 00:19:43,960
Tell me.

252
00:19:44,560 --> 00:19:47,520
What secret did you and Phupha discover?

253
00:19:58,320 --> 00:20:00,440
Kitti and Singha…

254
00:20:02,120 --> 00:20:03,760
They're dealing drugs.

255
00:20:07,320 --> 00:20:08,480
What?

256
00:20:10,040 --> 00:20:11,600
The two of them

257
00:20:12,520 --> 00:20:14,920
are hiding behind your authority,

258
00:20:15,680 --> 00:20:17,920
working with Superintendent Samuejai,

259
00:20:18,000 --> 00:20:19,680
turning wrong into right,

260
00:20:20,200 --> 00:20:22,520
and no one can stop them.

261
00:20:25,920 --> 00:20:29,120
The van taking promo records
to the radio stations

262
00:20:30,920 --> 00:20:31,920
got stopped by the police.

263
00:20:32,720 --> 00:20:34,360
I've been suspicious,

264
00:20:35,600 --> 00:20:37,960
why the company's vehicles

265
00:20:38,480 --> 00:20:40,200
keep getting stopped by the police.

266
00:20:42,760 --> 00:20:44,440
So this is what it's all about.

267
00:20:44,520 --> 00:20:46,600
We're not just saying this lightly.

268
00:20:47,120 --> 00:20:50,960
If you want proof,
you can ask Captain Tom.

269
00:21:05,560 --> 00:21:07,960
Why does it feel eerier today than usual?

270
00:21:11,960 --> 00:21:14,120
The atmosphere is perfect.

271
00:21:25,200 --> 00:21:27,200
Here I am, thinking I'm standing alone.

272
00:21:29,200 --> 00:21:30,520
Hello, Uncle!

273
00:21:30,600 --> 00:21:33,080
Even with your hat on, you look cool.

274
00:21:34,800 --> 00:21:36,520
I really am alone.

275
00:21:42,320 --> 00:21:43,880
The police helpline…

276
00:21:46,160 --> 00:21:48,280
It's in our village's chat group.

277
00:21:51,080 --> 00:21:52,320
I'll send it to this number.

278
00:22:04,200 --> 00:22:05,280
What the heck?

279
00:22:07,920 --> 00:22:09,520
Do they not know

280
00:22:10,160 --> 00:22:12,920
the message went to a dead person's phone?

281
00:22:14,800 --> 00:22:16,040
Whatever happens, happens.

282
00:22:19,040 --> 00:22:20,600
Uncle Sergeant. Uncle.

283
00:22:22,640 --> 00:22:25,600
If it's you, give me a lottery number.

284
00:22:26,120 --> 00:22:27,720
A lottery number, not a puppy!

285
00:22:34,720 --> 00:22:35,760
What?

286
00:22:46,760 --> 00:22:47,600
What's up, Au?

287
00:22:47,680 --> 00:22:48,600
Lieutenant.

288
00:22:49,120 --> 00:22:51,280
I just got a message
on Uncle Sergeant's phone.

289
00:22:51,360 --> 00:22:53,640
<i>Someone said there's going</i>
<i>to be a drug shipment.</i>

290
00:22:53,720 --> 00:22:54,880
A shipment?

291
00:22:54,960 --> 00:22:55,800
Yes.

292
00:22:55,880 --> 00:22:57,560
Forward it to Corporal Chom.

293
00:22:57,640 --> 00:22:59,360
Got it. I'll take care of it.

294
00:22:59,440 --> 00:23:00,680
Hey, Manat!

295
00:23:01,400 --> 00:23:02,840
You've been on the phone all this time.

296
00:23:03,520 --> 00:23:04,920
Why aren't you getting the ride ready?

297
00:23:06,240 --> 00:23:07,200
Talk later.

298
00:23:09,360 --> 00:23:12,520
-Are we ready?
-Yeah, the boss is ready.

299
00:23:13,680 --> 00:23:14,520
Hurry up!

300
00:23:19,960 --> 00:23:21,080
DARATHONG MUSIC

301
00:23:23,920 --> 00:23:25,040
So this is the truck.

302
00:23:38,080 --> 00:23:39,200
How's it going?

303
00:23:40,200 --> 00:23:41,560
Are the donations ready?

304
00:23:41,640 --> 00:23:43,480
Just waiting on the rest from the company.

305
00:23:43,560 --> 00:23:45,920
Here they are, old plushies and clothes.

306
00:23:46,000 --> 00:23:47,520
Load them into the truck, right?

307
00:23:47,600 --> 00:23:48,600
Yeah, put them on.

308
00:23:50,120 --> 00:23:51,160
I'll help.

309
00:24:08,520 --> 00:24:09,720
Hey!

310
00:24:10,560 --> 00:24:12,120
Don't touch that box.

311
00:24:13,520 --> 00:24:14,760
No.

312
00:24:14,840 --> 00:24:15,840
I'm just taking a break.

313
00:24:18,400 --> 00:24:19,240
Puna, anything else left?

314
00:24:19,320 --> 00:24:20,760
Just a little more inside.

315
00:24:21,880 --> 00:24:24,120
Tod and Tia, go help carry the rest.

316
00:24:24,200 --> 00:24:25,280
-Sure.
-Yes.

317
00:24:28,040 --> 00:24:29,600
Mr. Sonrak.

318
00:24:29,680 --> 00:24:33,600
Kamnan Pong called.
He said we need to prepare the venue.

319
00:24:33,680 --> 00:24:35,880
Alright, then let's go.

320
00:24:40,560 --> 00:24:42,440
Puna, let's get in the car.

321
00:24:43,120 --> 00:24:45,320
I'll follow in the pickup.

322
00:24:45,400 --> 00:24:46,360
Why?

323
00:24:47,840 --> 00:24:51,280
There are still old plushies
and clothes to load.

324
00:24:51,360 --> 00:24:53,120
Better to go with the pickup.

325
00:24:53,200 --> 00:24:55,880
We need to look after the donations.

326
00:24:56,960 --> 00:24:58,760
Got it. See you at the event.

327
00:25:00,320 --> 00:25:01,240
Let's go.

328
00:25:09,600 --> 00:25:11,440
Follow along in my car, Sophie.

329
00:25:11,520 --> 00:25:12,800
Okay, Miss Maria.

330
00:25:16,560 --> 00:25:18,960
Luckily we've got a private car.

331
00:25:19,040 --> 00:25:20,200
The AC's nice and cold.

332
00:25:25,000 --> 00:25:26,160
I told you already, didn't I?!

333
00:25:26,240 --> 00:25:29,360
Get the interest paid early.
My boss is in a hurry!

334
00:25:29,440 --> 00:25:30,960
I don't have the money yet.

335
00:25:31,040 --> 00:25:32,480
You're asking for it early.

336
00:25:32,560 --> 00:25:35,920
Please give me a couple of days
to finish harvesting, sir.

337
00:25:36,000 --> 00:25:38,240
My boss said today means today!

338
00:25:38,320 --> 00:25:40,600
Otherwise, we take your daughter
as collateral!

339
00:25:41,200 --> 00:25:42,720
Hey, go get her!

340
00:25:42,800 --> 00:25:44,360
-No! Don't!
-Hey!

341
00:25:44,440 --> 00:25:45,280
-Come here!
-Mom!

342
00:25:45,360 --> 00:25:46,640
-Don't take my daughter!
-Let's go!

343
00:25:46,720 --> 00:25:48,080
-Don't take my daughter!
-Let go!

344
00:25:48,160 --> 00:25:49,840
Don't take my daughter!

345
00:25:55,680 --> 00:25:58,280
Who the hell are you?
Stay back if you're not involved!

346
00:25:58,360 --> 00:26:01,360
I said back off, or I shoot!

347
00:26:02,160 --> 00:26:03,400
Leave the woman alone!

348
00:26:03,480 --> 00:26:06,280
Who the hell are you,
telling me to back off?

349
00:26:06,360 --> 00:26:08,160
You've messed with the wrong guy.

350
00:26:08,240 --> 00:26:09,120
You're dead!

351
00:26:10,440 --> 00:26:11,840
-Kill him!
-Mom!

352
00:26:18,320 --> 00:26:19,080
Take him out!

353
00:26:43,520 --> 00:26:44,880
Turned to mush!

354
00:26:48,960 --> 00:26:50,160
Ugh!

355
00:27:06,720 --> 00:27:08,760
Don't think you can bully the poor.

356
00:27:10,120 --> 00:27:12,360
Remember this until the day you die!

357
00:27:12,440 --> 00:27:14,400
Hey, get outta here!

358
00:27:26,400 --> 00:27:27,680
Thank you, sir.

359
00:27:27,760 --> 00:27:29,240
Thank you, Uncle.

360
00:27:30,040 --> 00:27:31,040
Good luck to you.

361
00:27:31,560 --> 00:27:32,480
Yes.

362
00:27:47,520 --> 00:27:48,720
How's everything here?

363
00:27:48,800 --> 00:27:50,200
All clear.

364
00:27:52,600 --> 00:27:55,560
You guys, check your weapons and ammo.

365
00:27:56,200 --> 00:27:58,000
If anyone acts suspicious,

366
00:27:58,920 --> 00:28:00,760
-shoot immediately.
-Yes.

367
00:28:02,800 --> 00:28:04,160
Where are we going?

368
00:28:04,760 --> 00:28:06,040
The boss has a new client.

369
00:28:07,440 --> 00:28:10,120
They're coming today
to inspect the sample.

370
00:28:11,120 --> 00:28:13,120
We need to clear the area first

371
00:28:13,200 --> 00:28:15,040
to prevent any complications.

372
00:28:15,120 --> 00:28:16,320
Complications?

373
00:28:16,400 --> 00:28:18,040
Yeah.

374
00:28:18,760 --> 00:28:20,760
We can't fully trust a new client.

375
00:28:21,280 --> 00:28:23,400
They might be police informants.

376
00:28:24,120 --> 00:28:26,000
So we clear the area beforehand.

377
00:28:26,080 --> 00:28:28,320
If anything suspicious happens,

378
00:28:28,920 --> 00:28:31,040
we can handle it immediately.

379
00:28:31,120 --> 00:28:31,960
Go.

380
00:28:32,600 --> 00:28:35,120
Split up and check the surroundings.

381
00:28:35,200 --> 00:28:36,200
-Yes.
-Yes.

382
00:28:37,160 --> 00:28:38,120
Let's go.

383
00:28:52,640 --> 00:28:54,680
Hey! Get out of here!

384
00:28:54,760 --> 00:28:55,960
Go away!

385
00:28:56,040 --> 00:28:58,880
Talk nicely! Why are you
chasing me like this?

386
00:28:58,960 --> 00:29:00,400
You wanna die? I'll slap you!

387
00:29:01,600 --> 00:29:03,880
Go ahead! You think that'll scare me?

388
00:29:03,960 --> 00:29:05,520
Take this! Hey!

389
00:29:06,560 --> 00:29:07,360
-Oh no!
-Ugh!

390
00:29:25,040 --> 00:29:26,320
You okay, Saijai?

391
00:29:26,400 --> 00:29:27,760
I'm fine, Uncle.

392
00:29:27,840 --> 00:29:30,800
I don't even know who these guys are.
They suddenly tried to chase

393
00:29:30,880 --> 00:29:32,640
and attack me.

394
00:29:32,720 --> 00:29:34,040
Remember this.

395
00:29:34,560 --> 00:29:37,000
No one has the right
to treat people like this in my village.

396
00:29:39,080 --> 00:29:40,120
Come on, Saijai.

397
00:29:45,960 --> 00:29:47,280
Follow him.

398
00:29:54,320 --> 00:29:55,440
CHECKPOINT

399
00:29:55,520 --> 00:29:56,720
What kind of vehicle are they using?

400
00:29:57,240 --> 00:30:00,160
A pickup truck. The drugs
are hidden in a box of plushies.

401
00:30:03,280 --> 00:30:04,840
Huh? Is that a checkpoint?

402
00:30:19,920 --> 00:30:20,840
What are you inspecting, Captain?

403
00:30:21,520 --> 00:30:23,560
Please step out of the vehicle.
We need to check the truck.

404
00:30:27,040 --> 00:30:28,040
Alright.

405
00:30:33,640 --> 00:30:34,760
Hello, Officer.

406
00:30:34,840 --> 00:30:36,080
-Hello.
-Hello.

407
00:30:36,160 --> 00:30:37,320
May I ask what you're checking?

408
00:30:37,400 --> 00:30:38,520
Drug inspection.

409
00:30:40,520 --> 00:30:42,080
You can pull your car aside.

410
00:30:42,680 --> 00:30:44,880
Huh? You're not checking our car?

411
00:30:44,960 --> 00:30:46,560
-It's not the target vehicle.
-I see.

412
00:30:47,360 --> 00:30:49,400
Then that pickup truck is the target?

413
00:30:50,800 --> 00:30:52,800
Go ahead. You can drive on.

414
00:30:53,320 --> 00:30:54,440
-Yes.
-Okay.

415
00:30:54,520 --> 00:30:55,720
Alright.

416
00:31:00,080 --> 00:31:02,320
CHECKPOINT

417
00:31:08,320 --> 00:31:09,280
Get out of the car.

418
00:31:11,080 --> 00:31:12,000
Hey.

419
00:31:13,680 --> 00:31:15,040
I know what to do now.

420
00:31:15,120 --> 00:31:16,240
Let's check it out.

421
00:31:37,440 --> 00:31:39,720
If the cops find the drugs in the box,

422
00:31:39,800 --> 00:31:42,160
Puna's finished for sure.
Don't you think?

423
00:31:42,240 --> 00:31:44,920
They're the ones who packed it.

424
00:31:45,000 --> 00:31:46,680
What chance does she have?

425
00:31:46,760 --> 00:31:48,200
Grab the camera! Shoot it!

426
00:31:48,280 --> 00:31:50,120
-Right, I forgot.
-Don't stop filming.

427
00:31:50,200 --> 00:31:52,280
-She's done for!
-Let me see her face

428
00:31:52,360 --> 00:31:53,640
when the police catch her.

429
00:32:00,360 --> 00:32:01,280
Found it, Captain!

430
00:32:08,520 --> 00:32:09,360
The informant said

431
00:32:10,720 --> 00:32:12,280
the box would be marked.

432
00:32:13,960 --> 00:32:15,120
Whose box is this?

433
00:32:16,560 --> 00:32:17,520
I don't know.

434
00:32:18,040 --> 00:32:19,160
Ask these two.

435
00:32:19,880 --> 00:32:20,920
I'm just the driver.

436
00:32:21,000 --> 00:32:23,840
They're done for. It's over.

437
00:32:24,480 --> 00:32:25,360
Alright, tell me.

438
00:32:26,120 --> 00:32:27,400
What's really in this box?

439
00:32:28,480 --> 00:32:31,080
Just plushies we're going to donate.

440
00:32:31,760 --> 00:32:32,840
This is your box, right?

441
00:32:32,920 --> 00:32:34,800
It's the company's box, not ours.

442
00:32:35,480 --> 00:32:38,560
But these two packed the donations
onto the truck.

443
00:32:40,200 --> 00:32:42,600
-She looks pale.
-So pale.

444
00:32:42,680 --> 00:32:43,880
Is it true

445
00:32:43,960 --> 00:32:47,040
that you two collected these items
and packed them into the box?

446
00:32:48,080 --> 00:32:49,280
You could say that, yes.

447
00:32:50,400 --> 00:32:53,480
Don't tell me
there's anything illegal in here.

448
00:32:55,600 --> 00:32:58,000
That's what I've been told. Open it.

449
00:33:07,560 --> 00:33:09,200
-It's too far.
-Just like that!

450
00:33:09,280 --> 00:33:10,560
-Zoom in!
-Exactly.

451
00:33:18,760 --> 00:33:20,320
What are you all doing?

452
00:33:29,320 --> 00:33:31,720
We received a tip
that this vehicle is carrying drugs.

453
00:33:32,840 --> 00:33:33,880
-Drugs?
-Drugs?

454
00:33:35,840 --> 00:33:37,040
Huh?

455
00:33:37,120 --> 00:33:38,160
Nonsense!

456
00:33:38,240 --> 00:33:41,120
This is Kamnan's donation vehicle.

457
00:33:41,200 --> 00:33:43,320
How could it possibly have drugs?

458
00:33:43,400 --> 00:33:44,720
We got a tip

459
00:33:44,800 --> 00:33:47,400
that drugs might be hidden
in these donation items.

460
00:33:47,480 --> 00:33:48,400
How is that possible?

461
00:33:49,440 --> 00:33:52,120
I've fought against drugs my whole life.

462
00:33:52,640 --> 00:33:55,560
How could donation items contain drugs?

463
00:33:57,040 --> 00:33:58,240
This is clearly an insult!

464
00:33:58,320 --> 00:34:02,320
He's going to give these plushies
to poor children.

465
00:34:02,400 --> 00:34:04,920
Are you seriously accusing him

466
00:34:05,000 --> 00:34:06,320
of trafficking drugs?

467
00:34:07,040 --> 00:34:08,560
Isn't that going too far?

468
00:34:10,360 --> 00:34:11,639
You guys.

469
00:34:11,719 --> 00:34:12,960
I think

470
00:34:13,040 --> 00:34:16,560
you're being used by his political rivals.

471
00:34:17,360 --> 00:34:19,199
They're trying to smear him

472
00:34:19,719 --> 00:34:22,600
and ruin his reputation
for political gain.

473
00:34:23,400 --> 00:34:24,719
If you believe them,

474
00:34:26,480 --> 00:34:28,199
it'll only cause trouble for him.

475
00:34:30,120 --> 00:34:31,520
Superintendent.

476
00:34:31,600 --> 00:34:33,880
What should we do?
Kamnan's reputation is at stake.

477
00:34:34,600 --> 00:34:36,639
I came here with him.

478
00:34:37,159 --> 00:34:39,320
Do you think I'm in on it too?

479
00:34:39,400 --> 00:34:40,320
No, sir.

480
00:34:40,400 --> 00:34:43,840
Then step aside.
We need to get to the event.

481
00:34:47,320 --> 00:34:49,400
The villagers are waiting
for the donations.

482
00:34:50,520 --> 00:34:52,600
Don't ruin it for them, okay?

483
00:34:55,520 --> 00:34:56,400
Hey!

484
00:34:56,480 --> 00:34:57,800
Let the truck go!

485
00:34:57,880 --> 00:34:59,880
You want to get disciplined or what?

486
00:35:01,440 --> 00:35:02,520
What do we do, Captain?

487
00:35:03,880 --> 00:35:04,720
Let the truck go.

488
00:35:05,440 --> 00:35:06,280
Put it back.

489
00:35:16,880 --> 00:35:18,880
We're missing out on content!

490
00:35:21,000 --> 00:35:22,560
Just make it fake news then.

491
00:35:34,160 --> 00:35:37,480
Sorry for the delay, Kamnan.

492
00:35:38,160 --> 00:35:42,240
Sometimes we should let them inspect,
to show we're honest.

493
00:35:42,760 --> 00:35:44,440
Doesn't hurt anyone, right?

494
00:35:44,960 --> 00:35:46,520
Well, let's get in the car.

495
00:35:47,040 --> 00:35:48,040
It's getting late.

496
00:35:48,120 --> 00:35:48,960
-Let's go.
-Let's go.

497
00:35:51,600 --> 00:35:52,360
What are you doing?

498
00:35:54,680 --> 00:35:55,680
Well…

499
00:35:57,720 --> 00:35:58,760
Yeah.

500
00:35:58,840 --> 00:36:00,560
We were filming Puna.

501
00:36:00,640 --> 00:36:02,960
She's been damaging
the company's reputation.

502
00:36:03,040 --> 00:36:05,480
You're the ones damaging my company!

503
00:36:07,360 --> 00:36:10,320
If any clips leak or fake news spreads,

504
00:36:10,400 --> 00:36:11,960
I'll throw you in jail

505
00:36:12,640 --> 00:36:14,440
and sue you to the last cent.

506
00:36:14,520 --> 00:36:17,360
Oh no! I'm not involved!

507
00:36:18,320 --> 00:36:19,320
Sophie told me to do it.

508
00:36:20,200 --> 00:36:23,360
Hey, who told you? I told you not to film!

509
00:36:23,440 --> 00:36:25,480
-Delete everything now!
-Got it.

510
00:36:25,560 --> 00:36:26,400
Okay.

511
00:36:27,240 --> 00:36:28,680
-Quickly!
-Hold on.

512
00:36:29,320 --> 00:36:31,000
Alright, done.

513
00:36:31,080 --> 00:36:32,920
All gone.

514
00:36:34,640 --> 00:36:36,680
You can go now. Move!

515
00:36:36,760 --> 00:36:37,800
-Yes!
-Let's go.

516
00:36:37,880 --> 00:36:38,960
Go!

517
00:36:44,240 --> 00:36:46,080
Uncle, they're following us!

518
00:36:46,160 --> 00:36:48,080
-Saijai, run!
-Hey, stop!

519
00:37:05,760 --> 00:37:06,760
Hey, Wong.

520
00:37:07,280 --> 00:37:08,720
Do you see him?

521
00:37:10,160 --> 00:37:11,840
He ran around here.

522
00:37:13,040 --> 00:37:14,800
Alright, search the area.

523
00:37:30,560 --> 00:37:31,720
Chart.

524
00:37:32,960 --> 00:37:34,360
What are you guys looking for?

525
00:37:34,440 --> 00:37:35,760
What business is it of yours?

526
00:37:37,240 --> 00:37:39,800
Is it the guy with the limp?

527
00:37:43,560 --> 00:37:44,920
You saw him?

528
00:37:45,640 --> 00:37:47,240
Yeah, I saw him heading that way.

529
00:37:48,440 --> 00:37:49,480
Follow him.

530
00:38:14,480 --> 00:38:15,360
Alright.

531
00:38:15,440 --> 00:38:16,880
Hey, Manat.

532
00:38:18,200 --> 00:38:19,840
-Come here.
-Just a sec.

533
00:38:19,920 --> 00:38:21,120
Hey.

534
00:38:21,200 --> 00:38:23,240
Are you disobeying Mr. Sonrak's orders?

535
00:38:24,760 --> 00:38:26,040
Come on!

536
00:38:39,680 --> 00:38:41,640
Are we unloading everything, Puna?

537
00:38:41,720 --> 00:38:44,080
-Yes. Let's move it to the donation table.
-Okay.

538
00:38:54,960 --> 00:38:55,840
Hey, wait!

539
00:38:56,560 --> 00:38:58,480
Leave that box. Unload the others.

540
00:38:59,560 --> 00:39:00,800
All boxes are the same.

541
00:39:01,880 --> 00:39:03,480
Not the same.

542
00:39:03,560 --> 00:39:04,880
I said the other boxes.

543
00:39:20,160 --> 00:39:21,280
Tod.

544
00:39:25,680 --> 00:39:26,680
Tia.

545
00:39:28,760 --> 00:39:29,840
Careful with it.

546
00:39:32,320 --> 00:39:33,320
Go ahead.

547
00:39:45,720 --> 00:39:46,680
Did you see him, Chart?

548
00:39:48,080 --> 00:39:49,320
No sign.

549
00:39:50,080 --> 00:39:52,840
We should head back to the meeting point.

550
00:39:53,360 --> 00:39:54,320
It's almost time.

551
00:39:55,560 --> 00:39:56,600
Then let's go.

552
00:40:12,120 --> 00:40:12,960
TEMPLE

553
00:40:17,320 --> 00:40:18,280
Where did that box go?

554
00:40:19,320 --> 00:40:20,640
Someone must've taken it already.

555
00:40:21,560 --> 00:40:23,760
If they had stacked it nearby,
we would've seen it.

556
00:40:24,640 --> 00:40:26,120
But it's not there.

557
00:40:26,200 --> 00:40:27,960
Then where did they take it?

558
00:40:28,040 --> 00:40:30,160
Don't worry about it.
Let's focus on our work.

559
00:40:30,880 --> 00:40:31,760
Okay.

560
00:40:42,320 --> 00:40:44,560
Hey, where did Chaiya go?

561
00:40:45,680 --> 00:40:46,520
He went with Chart.

562
00:40:48,040 --> 00:40:50,960
Earlier, the cops
set up a checkpoint for drugs.

563
00:40:51,040 --> 00:40:55,040
They tried to check the box,
but the superintendent stopped them.

564
00:40:56,120 --> 00:40:58,000
Then that box must have had drugs in it.

565
00:41:05,400 --> 00:41:07,000
FOOD AND SUPPLIES DONATION
FOR KHOK TA YU VILLAGERS

566
00:41:13,600 --> 00:41:14,640
Take it.

567
00:41:15,840 --> 00:41:17,800
Hurry, Manat, Puna!

568
00:41:17,880 --> 00:41:19,080
Get the supplies ready.

569
00:41:20,200 --> 00:41:21,080
We've been rushed.

570
00:41:30,400 --> 00:41:31,400
Here you go.

571
00:41:50,200 --> 00:41:51,280
Au.

572
00:41:52,920 --> 00:41:54,560
The cops let the drugs slip through.

573
00:41:55,160 --> 00:41:56,880
I don't know where they've been taken.

574
00:41:56,960 --> 00:41:57,840
Oh!

575
00:41:58,800 --> 00:42:00,160
What should we do?

576
00:42:00,680 --> 00:42:02,720
I haven't been able to reach
the captain yet.

577
00:42:02,800 --> 00:42:04,120
<i>I'll figure something out.</i>

578
00:42:04,200 --> 00:42:05,800
Stand by for now.

579
00:42:06,720 --> 00:42:07,560
Got it.

580
00:42:07,640 --> 00:42:09,720
If anything happens, call me immediately.

581
00:42:10,320 --> 00:42:11,200
Okay.

582
00:42:17,600 --> 00:42:19,000
Where did the captain go?

583
00:42:19,080 --> 00:42:21,280
Come on. Line up!

584
00:42:21,360 --> 00:42:23,560
-Come on.
-Men in front, elderly at the back.

585
00:42:23,640 --> 00:42:24,720
Hey, swap that!

586
00:42:25,240 --> 00:42:27,200
-Elderly go in front, men at the back.
-Right.

587
00:42:27,280 --> 00:42:29,680
-Put the kids first.
-Yeah, kids come here.

588
00:42:31,880 --> 00:42:33,000
Where is it?

589
00:42:37,480 --> 00:42:38,880
Where is it?

590
00:42:42,440 --> 00:42:43,920
Looking for something?

591
00:42:44,000 --> 00:42:45,880
Just a little something, you know.

592
00:42:47,000 --> 00:42:48,160
What exactly are you looking for?

593
00:42:50,600 --> 00:42:52,000
Looking for an unfaithful heart,

594
00:42:52,520 --> 00:42:54,400
running after someone who doesn't love me.

595
00:42:58,680 --> 00:42:59,800
Yeah sure!

596
00:43:14,280 --> 00:43:15,080
Puna.

597
00:43:15,160 --> 00:43:17,440
It's almost time. What are you doing here?

598
00:43:18,560 --> 00:43:19,840
I'm preparing the supplies.

599
00:43:19,920 --> 00:43:22,720
I think the teacher can handle this.
You come with me.

600
00:43:24,240 --> 00:43:25,280
Go ahead, Puna.

601
00:43:26,080 --> 00:43:28,240
I will take care of this.

602
00:43:29,480 --> 00:43:30,760
Alright, let's go.

603
00:43:44,240 --> 00:43:46,400
Sorry!

604
00:43:48,640 --> 00:43:51,560
Puna, could you hand out
the snacks to the kids?

605
00:43:51,640 --> 00:43:54,400
I'll take care of the villagers in line.

606
00:43:55,040 --> 00:43:57,160
I can have Puna help me instead.

607
00:43:57,240 --> 00:43:59,440
Well, Mr. Sonrak.

608
00:43:59,520 --> 00:44:02,440
Don't forget we're supposed
to be the cute couple for this event.

609
00:44:04,000 --> 00:44:06,120
Have Puna stand right here.

610
00:44:06,640 --> 00:44:10,120
If our fans see,
they might get mad at her.

611
00:44:10,200 --> 00:44:13,880
See? I'm just protecting Puna.

612
00:44:16,560 --> 00:44:18,040
Puna, is that okay?

613
00:44:18,120 --> 00:44:19,920
Yes, this spot is fine.

614
00:44:22,080 --> 00:44:24,920
Kamnan's here! Are you guys ready?

615
00:44:25,000 --> 00:44:27,040
-Yes!
-Ready!

616
00:44:27,120 --> 00:44:28,480
-Hello! Come on.
-Hello.

617
00:44:28,560 --> 00:44:29,480
Hey.

618
00:44:29,560 --> 00:44:30,640
Hello. Alright,

619
00:44:30,720 --> 00:44:31,960
if we're ready,

620
00:44:32,040 --> 00:44:34,840
let's start handing out
the donations. Come help!

621
00:44:35,560 --> 00:44:37,720
Kamnan, I need to speak
with the abbot first.

622
00:44:37,800 --> 00:44:39,400
I'll excuse myself too.

623
00:44:39,480 --> 00:44:42,320
I need to talk with the district officer.
I saw him over there.

624
00:44:43,520 --> 00:44:45,560
Why not help hand out the donations first?

625
00:44:46,880 --> 00:44:49,680
Please, Kamnan.
I'll take care of my business quickly.

626
00:44:51,200 --> 00:44:52,400
Suit yourself.

627
00:44:54,600 --> 00:44:55,920
Come on! Let's start.

628
00:44:56,000 --> 00:44:57,920
Come closer. Take this one, okay?

629
00:44:58,000 --> 00:44:59,000
Here you go!

630
00:45:00,600 --> 00:45:01,600
Alright.

631
00:45:02,880 --> 00:45:04,600
Here you go. Take this one.

632
00:45:04,680 --> 00:45:06,000
-Okay.
-It's fine. Take it.

633
00:45:06,080 --> 00:45:08,080
Take this one, okay?

634
00:45:08,160 --> 00:45:10,680
-Go ahead, hand them out!
-Exit this way.

635
00:45:14,440 --> 00:45:15,480
Go on.

636
00:45:15,560 --> 00:45:17,160
Alright, thanks a lot.

637
00:45:17,880 --> 00:45:18,760
Hey.

638
00:45:21,040 --> 00:45:22,120
What are you doing, Khod?

639
00:45:25,800 --> 00:45:26,960
Peeing.

640
00:45:34,200 --> 00:45:35,760
Come on. We're running late.

641
00:45:36,440 --> 00:45:37,480
Yes.

642
00:45:50,080 --> 00:45:51,000
What's up?

643
00:45:51,520 --> 00:45:54,360
Pleaw, he's coming to mess with us.

644
00:45:54,960 --> 00:45:57,560
These bastards just won't leave me alone!

645
00:45:58,160 --> 00:45:59,200
Don't worry.

646
00:45:59,280 --> 00:46:00,280
Let's go!

647
00:46:11,320 --> 00:46:12,240
Where have you been, Chart?

648
00:46:14,000 --> 00:46:14,840
I'll tell you in a bit.

649
00:46:18,240 --> 00:46:19,600
You checked the stuff thoroughly, right?

650
00:46:19,680 --> 00:46:22,040
Yes. Everything's inside, all set.

651
00:46:24,560 --> 00:46:25,680
Mr. Singha's here.

652
00:46:33,120 --> 00:46:34,640
Chart, Chit.

653
00:46:34,720 --> 00:46:35,640
-Yes.
-Yes.

654
00:46:36,760 --> 00:46:37,840
Chaiya.

655
00:46:38,720 --> 00:46:40,840
Keep watch for me.

656
00:46:40,920 --> 00:46:42,000
Something's definitely going to happen.

657
00:46:44,160 --> 00:46:45,840
Singha, the client is here.

658
00:46:46,640 --> 00:46:47,480
Boss Jiang.

659
00:46:48,200 --> 00:46:50,960
Pleasure to meet you,
Mr. Singha. Mr. Kitti.

660
00:46:51,480 --> 00:46:52,440
Yes.

661
00:46:53,280 --> 00:46:54,720
I've prepared the goods for today.

662
00:47:27,920 --> 00:47:28,760
Well.

663
00:47:29,280 --> 00:47:30,160
Aren't you going to count it?

664
00:47:30,240 --> 00:47:31,520
No need, sir.

665
00:47:31,600 --> 00:47:33,400
We trust you completely.

666
00:47:34,880 --> 00:47:37,080
-Glad to do business together.
-Yes.

667
00:47:37,160 --> 00:47:38,560
Likewise. It's a pleasure.

668
00:47:38,640 --> 00:47:41,040
When we have time, Singha and I

669
00:47:41,120 --> 00:47:43,600
will cross the border to visit you.

670
00:47:43,680 --> 00:47:45,400
I hope you don't mind.

671
00:47:45,480 --> 00:47:47,120
Of course! Please come!

672
00:47:47,200 --> 00:47:49,080
We'll take good care of you.

673
00:47:49,160 --> 00:47:50,320
Thank you.

674
00:47:53,480 --> 00:47:54,800
-Take cover!
-Go!

675
00:47:58,320 --> 00:47:59,280
Get down!

676
00:48:04,360 --> 00:48:06,600
He works as Mr. Sonrak's driver.

677
00:48:06,680 --> 00:48:08,160
Even if you're a good person,

678
00:48:09,080 --> 00:48:10,640
I can't fully trust you.

679
00:48:10,720 --> 00:48:11,560
NEXT EPISODE

680
00:48:11,640 --> 00:48:12,560
Take her with us!

681
00:48:15,400 --> 00:48:17,920
What is Puna doing
at Boss Nok's music label?

682
00:48:18,000 --> 00:48:19,720
Is she switching labels?

683
00:48:19,800 --> 00:48:22,960
But I work in wardrobe, not as an actor.

684
00:48:23,040 --> 00:48:25,760
I need to save as much budget as possible.

685
00:48:25,840 --> 00:48:27,200
You take this role

686
00:48:27,720 --> 00:48:29,360
and handle both wardrobe and acting.

687
00:48:33,200 --> 00:48:35,480
Puna still hasn't arrived?

688
00:51:35,040 --> 00:51:37,040
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
